::Ramulus::

His face still white, Ramulus prepares for reentry, ceasing to breathe as the 
shuttle begins to decend. He clenches his teeth, suddenly wishing that they 
would just have stayed on the moon and gone back some easier way. 
Teleportation, perhaps... It should have taken more than 20 or so years to 
build a suitable device!

He keeps quiet, not trusting himself to open his mouth.
